    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="298"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1497.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-07-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 31, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your interesting despatch of the 13th instant,
                    No. 1014, relative to the feeling evinced towards the United States during the
                    recent elections which have taken place in England, has been received. Those
                    elections, so far as they indicate sympathy with our national cause and promise
                    progress in liberal ideas, are highly gratifying, and your remarks upon the
                    dependence of those ideas upon the course of events here are judicious, and I
                    trust will be duly appreciated.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c. London.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
